this example show how to use the hybrid axisem/specfem code. 
After instalation and compilation run in matlab 

Hybrid_Axisem_Specfem

in menu file->import config 
  load chunk_param_exemple_1.mat

this is an exemple of 10° x 5° x 240 km chunk for 10 s minmum period. 

  click on :
   -- Read Stations 
       then load stations.profil1
   -- mesh 
   -- decompose (choose the number of proc for specfem) 
   -- database

   then prepare databases for tractions 
   
    --MESH (AxiSEM) use 10s dominand period and choose number of mpi processes for axisem
    --SOLVE give a name for running directory that not exist yet. (It will be created)
     --choose the time window and time step to store tractions 

 

**** THIS EXEMPLE REQUIRE 15 Go DISK TO STORE ALL FILES NEEDED TO RUN THE HYBRID METHOD *****
